# Storefront App

## Purpose

The `storefront` app is the customer-facing commerce experience for storefront browsing and checkout.
It is distinct from the marketing site in `apps/web`.

## Structure

```text
apps/storefront/src/
├── app/
│   ├── [lang]/
│   │   ├── layout.tsx
│   │   ├── page.tsx
│   │   ├── products/[id]/page.tsx
│   │   └── checkout/
│   └── api/storefront/[[...rest]]/route.ts
├── components/
│   ├── app/
│   ├── layout/
│   └── shared/
├── shared/
│   ├── api/                   # orpc client, error-handler, mutations, queries
│   │   ├── orpc.ts            # oRPC client export
│   │   ├── error-handler.ts   # Centralized `handleAPIError`
│   │   ├── mutations.ts       # `appMutations` (order.create, store.subscribeToLaunch)
│   │   └── queries.ts         # `appQueries` (cart.items)
│   ├── config/                # App-wide configuration
│   │   ├── constants.ts       # Typed storefront constants
│   │   ├── i18n.ts            # Locale helpers and i18n config
│   │   └── routes.ts          # Type-safe route definitions
│   └── lib/                   # Domain-organized business logic
│       ├── cart/              # enricher.hook.ts, item-comparator.ts, store.ts
│       ├── product/           # variant-selector.hook.ts
│       ├── store/             # slug-retrieval.util.ts
│       └── address-detection.hook.ts
├── env.ts
└── proxy.ts
```

## Data and API

- Use `appQueries` and `appMutations` from `@/shared/api/queries` and `@/shared/api/mutations`.
- The underlying oRPC client is in `@/shared/api/orpc.ts`.
- Keep request and response typing aligned with shared schemas from `@dukkani/common`.
- Route API calls through `app/api/storefront/[[...rest]]/route.ts` when app-local API entry is needed.

```typescript
// Fetching data
import { useQuery } from "@tanstack/react-query";
import { appQueries } from "@/shared/api/queries";

const { data: cartItems } = useQuery(appQueries.cart.items({ input: { storeId } }));
```

```typescript
// Mutating data
import { useMutation } from "@tanstack/react-query";
import { appMutations } from "@/shared/api/mutations";

const mutation = useMutation(appMutations.order.create());
const subscribeMutation = useMutation(appMutations.store.subscribeToLaunch());
```

## State Management

- Cart and filter state lives in Zustand stores under `shared/lib/{domain}/store.ts`.
- Derive computed cart values in selectors or utility functions within the domain folder, not in UI components.

```typescript
// Cart store
import { useCartStore } from "@/shared/lib/cart/store";

// Cart enrichment hook (combines cart store with server product data)
import { useEnrichedCart } from "@/shared/lib/cart/enricher.hook";
```

## i18n and Routing

- Keep user-visible routes under `app/[lang]/...`.
- Use locale helpers from `@/shared/config/i18n` and keep locale-aware links consistent.
- Type-safe routes available from `@/shared/config/routes`.

## Error Handling

- Use `handleAPIError` from `@/shared/api/error-handler.ts` for all error handling.
- Do not inline generic error toasts; keep error mapping centralized.
- `appMutations` factories automatically wire `onError` to `handleAPIError` — extend rather than replace.

## Best Practices

- Use server components by default and opt into `"use client"` only when needed.
- Keep checkout, cart, and product-card logic modular in `components/app/`.
- Reuse UI primitives from `@dukkani/ui`.
- Keep storefront-specific logic in this app and shared cross-app logic in packages.
- File suffix conventions in `shared/lib/`:
  - `controller.hook.ts` / `.hook.ts` — React hooks
  - `.util.ts` — pure utility functions
  - `.store.ts` — Zustand store definitions
